  <summary>6/5/2008--Introduced.
Designates June 6, 2008, as a national day of prayer and rededication for the men and women of the United States Armed Forces and their mission. Encourages Americans to join the Senate in such national day by reflecting on President Roosevelt's D-Day radio prayer.</summary>
